div.p: William Odgers to Libraries in Victoria
No. 2172, unit 42, pp. 1213-14, VPRS 1187/P outward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office, Victoria.

p.style: font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt;

p.seg: The Chief Secretary has previously transmitted to you the First and Second Parts of the Government Botanist's Educational Collection of Botanical Specimens for deposit in your Library. Baron von Mueller now reports that Part III. is in a forward state of preparation and will be ready for issue in the course of a few days. It is not proposed to distribute this Part indiscriminately, but to present it (and future issues) only to so many of the Public Libraries supplied with Parts I. and II. as make application for the same, and thus indicate due appreciation of the labor bestowed on the preparation of the Collections, as well as of its utility for the purposes of reference.

p.style: font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in;

div.p: I have the honor to be,
